reviews.text: The service was excellent. The chef will explain what items are included in each course, and will tell you some fun facts about the food of choice as well as some suggested ways or sequence when eating. Overall, the food quality was spot on, albeit its price ($1300). Although the portion of each course is small, there are lots of courses so you won't leave the restaurant with an empty stomach. I'm very much satisfied by the wide variety of dishes and the food was well prepared. I would definitely recommend anyone who are looking for a high quality dinner and are ready for a hefty price tag to come here.
Excellent service and good quality of food. Highly recommend!
Best omakase I have ever eaten. Top notch staff. Will for sure miss this a lot!!

Best and most authentic Japanese restaurant in Hong Kong. They import fish fresh from Tsukiji every day. Kei-san (the owner and also a chef) is amazing. I’ve been a long term customer of theirs and have tried all the top Japanese restaurants in HK (including the couple of Michelin star ones in the city), and this is still my favorite.
Personal attention to service.  Also fish I have never seen before
